07/07/2004
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Deputy Prime Minister Radmila Sekerinska and Norwegian Ambassador to Macedonia Dag Halvorsen signed two memorandums of understanding Tuesday (6 July). 
They call for Norway to disburse a total of 3.7m euros, aimed at supporting Macedonia's European integration efforts and reforming public administration, as spelled out in the Ohrid Framework Agreement.
In other news, the main Macedonian opposition party VMRO-DPMNE says it will stage three days of protests against the government's power decentralisation reform package. 
VMRO-DPMNE opposes the new territorial division and the proposed requirement that the Skopje City Council use two official languages. 
(MIA, Makfax, A1 TV - 06/07/04)
